.                               => focus object/ move privot back to middle of screen
Alt + Z                         => X-Ray Mode.

Blender Setting :
-----------------
    File >> Preference >> Interface >> Resulationo = 1.2
    Edit >> Preference >> KeyMap >> 3d view >> 3d view (Global) >> Change (Rotate, Pane, Zoom)
    Edit >> Preference >> KeyMap >> 3d view >> Mesh >> Mesh (Global) >> Loop Select >> change (left + double click)

Backface Culling :
------------------
    Face Orientation >> Enable to check Backface culling
    Mesh >> Goto edit mode >> Overlays >> Normals >> enable eny normal to check current face

Add ons : 
---------
    File >> Preference >> Add Ons
    Install Extra Extra Curve 
    Install Extra Object >> Shift + A >> Rock Genarator
    Install A.N.T Landscape >> Shift + A >> Landscape

Quad View :
-----------
    Ctrl + Alt + Q              => To Open Quad view.

Local view :
------------
    /       => Hide everything except what we select

Mode :
------
    Tab             => Toggle between Object/Edit Mode.
    1/2/3           => Vertex/Edeg/Face mode in Edit Mode.

Transform :
-----------
    G                                   => To select Move mode.
    R                                   => To select Rotate mode.
    S >> Shift + Z                      => S to goto Scale mode and ignore Z axis scale.

Secect :
--------
    AA                          => Deselect all.
    B                           => Box Select mode.
    C                           => Circle Select mode. Change size of circle using mouse scroll. Middle mouse for deselect.
    W                           => Change Select Mode.

    Ctrl + L                    => Linked Select.
    alt + click                 => Loop Select. Modify Version : Alt + double click.
    Ctrl + Plus                 => Grow Select.

    F3                          => First select some faces and then press F3 and search SELECT SIMILER.
    F3                          => First select some faces and then press F3 and search SELECT CIRCLE.


Sculpting :
-----------
    F                           => Press F and then drag mouse for change brush size.
    Shift + F                   => Press Shift + F and then drag mouse for change brush Strength size.

Hide :
------
    H                           => Hide object or selected object.
    Atl + H                     => get back to that object.

Delete :
-------
    ctrl + x                    => Select vertecis and delete.





Extrude :
---------
    E                           => Select face and press e to extrude.
    alt + E                     => Open Extrude option for like (Extrude along normal).
    ctrl + Right click          => Extrude any point in 3d space.

Loop Cut :
----------
    Ctrl + r                    => Select loop cut and mouse while will increse loop cut.

Bavel :
-------
    Ctrl + b                    => For edge bavel 
    Ctrl + shift + b            => For vertex bavel. round around vertex not edges.

Knife :
-------
    K                           => Then select some cut and to exit hit "Enter / Space"

Marge :
-------
    m                           => Select all vertex and M to marge object
                                => Then select vertex and extrude or ctrl + left click.

Inset :
------
    I                           => Inset.

Proportional Editing :
----------------------
    O                           => Open proportional editing.
    G                           => Then use scroll while to change proportional editing circle.

Flaten serface : 
-----------------
    F3                          => Select some faces then F3 and type flatten

Normals :
---------
    Mesh tab >> Normals / Alt + n           => Select wrong face and flip normal.


Triangle :
----------
    ctrl + f                => Trianglur faces.


Modifire :
----------
    Remash                  => Keep object as it is and add subdivision.




Unrap UV Map :
---------------
    Select Object >> goto edit mode >> select all vertex / select all >> uv tab >> select "smart uv project" or something else




Add tow texture into one mesh :
-------------------------------
    Edit >> Preference >> Add-ons >> Import image on plane
    File >> Import >> image as plane
    Add modifer >> Shrinkwarp
    Shrinkwarp :
    ------------
        Wrape mode >> project
        Target >> select target object where to put current plane image
        Set Ofset

    Use Texture Paint to Drow sticker  :
    ------------------------------------
        Select Texture >> Mapping "Stencil" [Alt for rotate and shift for scale]

    

Texture Paint : 
---------------
    ctrl + tab              => Select "Texture Paint"
    alt + s                 => save image

    UV :
    ---
        Select mesh >> goto edit mode >> select al vertex >> Unwrap UV Map

    Create Texture :
    ----------------
        Active Tool and workspace setting Tab >> Texture Slot >> Set "Mode" to "Single Texture" >> New >> Cteate new texture

    Create Material :
    -----------------
        Material Tab >> Create new material
        Click Base color >> Select Image Texture >> Assaign texture which we create avobe

    Add Texture to paint :
    ----------------------
        Texture Tab >> New texture >> assign texture as much as need

    For Paint :
    -----------
        Active Tool and workspace setting Tab >> Set color to white
        Active Tool and workspace setting Tab >> Open texture >> select texture to paint
    
    Mask Paintaing :
    ----------------
        Mask use only certain part of model to paint
        Enable Paint mask >> select model >> Edit mode >> select face for plaint


Bake Texture : 
--------------
    Select Object and Unwrap UV
    Create and assaign material to object
    On Shader graph add "Image Texture" and create a texture
    Select Object and select "Image Texture" on shader graph 
    Select Render property tab >> Engin Cycle >> Click Bake dropdown (blow) >> click bake


Create Cave :
-------------
    Create Cube then extrude one face (Using Ctrl + left click to create cave structure)
    Then after create cave structure add Subdivition Surface 
    Also add Displace and add Stucci image type from Texture Property and adjust size 
    and adjust Strength and Direction property form Displace modifer
    for low poly use Dacimate modifer

HightMap for Everionment :
---------------------------
    Create plane and edit then subdivide 
    Select Render property tab >> Engin Cycle 
    Create material for plane >> goto material tab >> Setting >> Displacement = Displacement only
    On Shader graph add "Image Texture" and add HightMap texture >> color Space = liner
    On Shader graph add "Displacement" and output >> "Material Output" >> Displacement
    HightMap Texture color output = Displacement hight input



Curve to custom shape :
-----------------------
    shift + A then select curve and only feawer curve avalabel then goto edit >> Preference >> add ons >> search >> Extra curve and install
    select curve and create shape

    >>  Object data poperty >> Geometry >> Increace Depth and this will create pipe type object

    Another way to convart curve to mesh
    ------------------------------------
    >>  Add plane >> Select object >> select Convert >> curve
    >>  Select curve we want ot convart to object >> Object data poperty Tab >> Geometry >> Object >> Select plane we just create

    Another way to convart curve to mesh
    ------------------------------------
    >> Select curve and create shape
    >> create a cube scale and subdivide or loop cut enough to bend then add curve modifer and select curve shape we create
        Then select axis to bend.


Export FBX :
------------
    File >> External Data >> Unpack All Into File >> Chose current file path
    [This will create "Texture" folder and put all texter into this folder]
    
    File >> Export as >> FBX >> [Select Current object, Apply Transform, chose mesh] >> Export

    Then Take "Texture" folder and fbx file into unity.



Flat shade for Low poly model : 
-------------------------------
    Select Object >> left Click >> Flat shade


IF UV editor or material not showing then select all vertex and UV tab >> reset.
